 :tx/provenance :observed
 :tx/rationale "AUDIT-W3-004: Replace secondary index cloning with index-by-offset architecture. PROBLEM: store.rs:1063 index_datom() clones each Datom 4-5 times into secondary indexes (entity_index, attribute_index, vaet_index, avet_index, live_view). A Datom is ~200-500 bytes (EntityId + Attribute(String) + Value(enum with String/Vec) + TxId + Op). At 123K datoms with 5x cloning: ~100-250MB RAM vs ~25-55MB with offset-based indexes. First principle: store data once, reference it many times. SOLUTION: (1) Store datoms in a Vec<Datom> (primary, append-only, index-stable). (2) Secondary indexes store usize offsets into the Vec instead of cloned Datoms. (3) entity_index: BTreeMap<EntityId, Vec<usize>>. attribute_index: BTreeMap<AttributeId, Vec<usize>>. (4) Lookup: index → offset → &datoms[offset]. Zero cloning. (5) BTreeSet<Datom> → Vec<Datom> changes the deduplication strategy: use a HashSet<DatomHash> for O(1) membership checking. VERIFICATION: (1) Memory benchmark: < 60MB for 123K datoms. (2) All existing tests pass. (3) proptest: index lookup results identical to scan results. (4) Merge still works (set union on hash sets). DEPENDS-ON: W3-003 (Attribute interning makes offset-based keys smaller). INTERACTS-WITH: Changes Store's internal representation — affects every store consumer. Large refactor."
